### [Proverbs Chapter 3](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 3:1](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">pro 3:1</span></span>

My law - The law of God, which might be called his law, as the gospel is
called Paul's gospel, [Ti2 2:8](../../../bib/kjv/ti2002.htm#008.md),
because delivered by him.

[Proverbs 3:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 3:3</span></span>

Mercy - Mercy denotes all benignity, charity, and readiness to do good
to others: truth or faithfulness respects all those duties which we owe
to God or man, which we have special obligation from the rules of
justice. Bind them - Like a chain, wherewith persons adorn their necks.
Table - In thy mind and heart, in which all God's commands are to be
received and engraven.

[Proverbs 3:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 3:4</span></span>

Understanding - Whereby to know thy duty, and to discern between good
and evil. Of God - Grace or favour with God, and that understanding
which is good in God's sight.

[Proverbs 3:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">pro 3:5</span></span>

Trust - Wholly rely upon God's promises and providences. Lean not -
Under this one kind of carnal confidence, he understands all other
confidence in bodily strength, wealth, or friends.

[Proverbs 3:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 3:8</span></span>

Navel - To thy body, which is signified by one part of it. Marrow -
Which is the nourishment and strength of the bones.

[Proverbs 3:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 3:9</span></span>

Substance - Lay out thy estate not to please thyself, but to glorify
God. First - fruits - Or, with the chief or best; which answers to the
first - fruits under the law.

[Proverbs 3:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 3:10</span></span>

So - This is not the way to diminish thy estate, but rather to increase
it.

[Proverbs 3:11](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">pro 3:11</span></span>

Despise not - Either by making light of it, or not being duly affected
with it; or by accounting it an unnecessary thing: but rather esteem it
a privilege and favour from God. Weary - Neither think it tedious or
hard, but endure it with patience and chearfulness.

[Proverbs 3:13](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">pro 3:13</span></span>

Findeth - Which supposes his diligent searching for it.

[Proverbs 3:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 3:17</span></span>

Peace - Procure a blessed tranquility in a man's mind and conscience.

[Proverbs 3:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 3:18</span></span>

A tree - A pledge of everlasting life. He alludes to the tree of life,
and intimates, that this is the only restorer of that life which we have
lost by sin.

[Proverbs 3:19](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">pro 3:19</span></span>

Wisdom - Either by Christ, or by that Divine perfection of wisdom, which
is the fountain of wisdom in man.

[Proverbs 3:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 3:20</span></span>

The depths - That great abyss contained in the bowels of the earth,
breaks forth into fountains and rivers.

[Proverbs 3:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 3:21</span></span>

Eyes - The eyes of thy mind. Constantly and seriously meditate upon
them.

[Proverbs 3:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 3:22</span></span>

Grace - Like a beautiful chain or ornament.

[Proverbs 3:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">pro 3:25</span></span>

Be not - Thou shalt not be afraid. Sudden - For sudden and unexpected
evils are most frightful. And fear is here put for the evils feared.
Desolation - Which cometh upon the wicked.

[Proverbs 3:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 3:26</span></span>

Shall be - A sure ground of confidence to thee. Taken - In the snares
either of sin or mischief.

[Proverbs 3:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#027.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_027">pro 3:27</span></span>

With - hold not - Do not deny it, but readily and chearfuly impart it.
Good - Any thing which is good, either counsel, comfort, reproof, or the
good things of the present life. Due - That is, to all men, by that
great and sovereign law of love.

[Proverbs 3:28](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">pro 3:28</span></span>

Say not - The former verse forbad the denial, and this forbids the delay
of this duty.

[Proverbs 3:29](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#029.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_029">pro 3:29</span></span>

Securely - Relying upon thine integrity.

[Proverbs 3:31](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">pro 3:31</span></span>

Envy not - For his impunity and success.

[Proverbs 3:32](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#032.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_032">pro 3:32</span></span>

Abomination - Therefore sooner or later he must be miserable. The
righteous - They are God's friends, to whom he imparts the favours and
comforts to which other men are strangers.

[Proverbs 3:33](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#033.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_033">pro 3:33</span></span>

The house - Not only upon his own person, but also upon his posterity.

[Proverbs 3:35](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#035.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_035">pro 3:35</span></span>

Shame - Instead of that glory which they seek.

